	<h3>CSS / Sass</h3>
	<p>Kickoff provides many variables and sensible defaults (colour palette, fonts, grid settings and more) so you can start writing code as quickly as possible. To take advantage of the full power of this, it is advised that you start each project by defining your own defaults. See below for how to do this:</p>
	<div class="well">

		<h4>Project variables</h4>

		<label class="checkbox">
			<input type="checkbox">
			Define your colour scheme
		</label>
		<div class="checklistInfo">
			Open <code>/scss/_colour-palette.scss</code> and change any vars to your own ones.
		</div>

		<h5>Open <code>/scss/_variables.scss</code></h5>
		<label class="checkbox">
			<input type="checkbox">
			Define your font sizes
		</label>
		<div class="checklistInfo">
			<ul>
				<li>Lines 17-23 define your base font size and your heading sizes.</li>
				<li>Lines 25, 26 define the leading and line-height.</li>
				<li>If your webfont's bold font-weight is not <code>700</code>, change this value to the weight you are using.</li>
			</ul>
		</div>

		<label class="checkbox">
			<input type="checkbox">
			Define your font stacks
		</label>
		<div class="checklistInfo">
			<ul>
				<li>Lines 34-36 define your base font stacks. These are used throughout the framework.</li>
				<li><code>$base-font-family</code> is used for the default typeface so make sure you update it's value with one of the font-stacks above.</li>
				<li><code>$headings-font-family</code> is used for headings typeface. The default value, <code>inherit</code>, means that it will inherit from <code>$base-font-family</code> so if you don't want that, make sure to change it.</li>
				<li>If your heading's webfont bold font-weight is not <code>700</code>, change this value to the weight you are using.</li>
			</ul>
		</div>

		<label class="checkbox">
			<input type="checkbox">
			Define your breakpoints
		</label>
		<div class="checklistInfo">
			<ul>
				<li>Define your own breakpoints to suit your design, the defaults here are just a suggestion</li>
				<li><code>$breakpoint-single-col</code> is a convenience breakpoint for use when you want to switch from a single column (on mobile) to a muliple columns (on desktop).</li>
				<li>An example usage for these might be:
<pre><code>@include respond-min($breakpoint-single-col) {
// RWD code
}</code></pre>
				</li>
			</ul>
		</div>

		<label class="checkbox">
			<input type="checkbox">
			Define your path variables
		</label>
		<div class="checklistInfo">
			It can be useful to save certain paths as variables to ease development, especially image paths
		</div>

		<label class="checkbox">
			<input type="checkbox">
			Setup the grid
		</label>
		<div class="checklistInfo">
			Kickoff comes with a grid system, the Choreographic Grid. To define your grid column count, gutter widths etc change the vars from lines 73-87.
		</div>

		<label class="checkbox">
			<input type="checkbox">
			Define some global app-specific variables
		</label>
		<div class="checklistInfo">
			On line 95 there is one example of an app-specific variable, this is for link transitions. Add any others that you may need below there.
		</div>
	</div>

	<h3>All done!</h3>
	<p>Now run <code>grunt watch</code> or <code>grunt serve</code> and start creating magic!</p>
